<div id="c28">
<p>Grow up.</p>

<p>I know that sounds combative and insulting, but it is intended to be neither, and is probably the most productive comment you&#8217;ll receive.</p>

<p>I&#8217;m simply reacting to what sounds like a need for better coping skills, and to adapt to and see the positives in change. As it is your cheese has been moved &#8212; to reference a terribly overused meme, so you&#8217;re feeling vulnerable and negative about everything around you. In many ways this almost reads like the first letter home from summer camp, when everything stinks and is yucky and everyone is mean and &#8220;can&#8217;t you come and pick me up mom?&#8221;</p>

<p>Did you ever go away to summer camp? Did you go away for university?</p>

<p>Of course, empire-building asshat IT departments and policies are an epic annoyance in this industry. They&#8217;re basically a set of policies built around keeping Timmy &#8220;the gator&#8221; in sales from opening viruses disguised an porn email, but they&#8217;re a major pain in the ass for people who know what they&#8217;re doing.</p>

